summary: Two simple dll files For those who recently updated the windows 10 and having trouble to open any software through MO.
descriptionHtml:
Two simple dll files For those[color=#ff0000] [u]who recently updated the windows 10[/u][/color] and having trouble to open any software through MO..


If you open [s]skse[/s](any software through MO) and those errors pop out, this is the solution for you.

[img]data:image/png;base64,[/img]
[img]data:image/png;base64,[/img]

[s]Download the file and put it in the root of the game file(Or where your skse_loader.exe at).

[/s][color=#ff0000]Put it where your executable at.[/color]

For examples:

having problems with SKSE, put into the directory of skse_loader.exe.

having problems with LOOT, put into the directory of LOOT.exe.

etc..

[b]Explanation:[/b]

[s]It seems like the newest version of MSVCR120.dll and MSVCP120.dll from VC 2013 updated by Microsoft can not be used by skse.

[/s]It is the problem caused by Mod Organizer, not SKSE's fault or any other executable files fault.

Apparently MO self contained older dll files in it's directory, that can not be used to open another executable which using the whatever version of dll files your computer has. So the solution here is to let them using the same version and the problem is gone.



[s]So, here are the older version of MSVCR120.dll and MSVCP120.dll.
Simply put the file in the root of the game file and you are good to go. [/s]

[u][b]Warning: If you are using x86 system rather than x64 system. I am not sure this will work(I'm not an expert). But give it a try :)

Do not, under any circumstance to replace your MSVCP120.dll and MSVCR120.dll in C:\WINDOWS\SYSTEM32. You should only place the older version in the same directory as your executable is.(Thank you toÂ [/b][/u][u][b] [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/524928]NeoH4x0r[/url] for pointing this out.)[/b][b]
[/b][/u]
